name: Air Fried Vegetarian "Chicken Tenders"
author: Chef Wheeler del Torro
summary: Great-grandma's timeless recipe for crispy fried 'chicken.' The best part: because it is adapted for an air fryer, it's a healthier version compared to its fried cousin! Serve with honey-mustard sauce for dipping.
ingredients: 2 (16 ounce) packages imitation chicken breast halves (seitan), cut into 1-inch wide strips
directions: Pour flour onto a large plate
Place eggs in a shallow bowl
Combine bread crumbs, garlic powder, paprika, cayenne pepper, black pepper, chili powder, and salt in another shallow bowl
Coat imitation chicken strips in flour, dip into eggs, then dredge in bread crumb mixture, and place on a plate
Heat an air fryer to 500 degrees F (260 degrees C)
Place a row of coated strips in the air fryer basket
Spray with a light coat of cooking spray
Cook strips in the air fryer for 6 minutes
Open fryer to flip strips with tongs
Continue cooking until golden brown, 4 to 6 minutes more
